ENCHANTER BUILDS FROM WHAT WE KNOW SO FAR
 

The Enchanters of Pantheon are going to love what VR has built for them. We are going to look at some build options, to give the community so options depending on there play style as Pantheon has a large array of options!
 

Charmer – The Enchanter has many forms of Mez, but none stronger than the Charm. Taking an enemy foe, and manipulating it to fight for your side has no parallel! I’m so excited to see Pantheon has carried this ability over from its predecessor EQ, EQOA, and EQ 2(Coercer). A talented enchanter can charm an enemy mob, use it for the time being, and then dismiss it at will, adding increased damage, tank-ability, a scape goat if things get to heavy to handle, it’s amazing! This is the only Caster, outside the Paladin who has this capability. You won’t see many offensive spells in this build as your Charmed Pet is your offense, and you can control the flow of battle in the mean while.

 

Primary Stat – Int (Charm is directly effected by Int, plus it will raise the base damage of your magic spells)

 

Secondary Stats – Char/Con (Both these stats effect charm. Building both pools will also assist in your longevity in prolonged encounters)

 

1.       Charm

You attempt to infiltrate your target’s mind, allowing you to take control of them for X duration. The chance of a successful Charm and the length of time the Charm will last can be improve based on your Intelligence, Constitution and Charisma. (Well duh, this is the spell we are basing our build around. It is such a strong spell! As you venture into Terminus, you will cross paths with many foes. Having a charmed one on your side during any encounter, equal level to the mob your trying to kill…. It’s unstoppable! Just be aware over long periods of time this spell could break, so a recast at some point may be required.)

 

2.     Dire Charm

Epic Ability. Enchanters can evolve their Charm ability into Dire Charm, which is harder for your target to resist and has an innate chance of permanently charming your target. This chance will stack with Mental Terraformer. Permanent charm will break when you die or zone. (The opportunity for the mob to become permanent, with no recasts needed, it so strong it’s almost OP!)

 

3.     Illusion Graft: Acuity

You graft an illusion into your ally’s mind, granting them an increased sense of mental acuity. While active, your ally’s Spell-Casting Speed will be increased by X%. (A great buff if you find a caster to Charm! It will also be useful on DPs or Healers in the group!)

 

4.     Enshire’s Faint Whisper

You enchant your ally’s mind with serenity, causing them to relax and allowing their Mana to regenerate more quickly. (A very cool buff for the main healer in the group, it’s a must have!)

 

5.      Rend the Mind

You rend your target’s mind with a burst of mental energy, dealing Magic damage and restoring some Mana to you and your group members.(This is great with your increased Int your base mana regen back to your group will be much appreciated!)

 

6.     Hush

Silences your enemy, making them unable to cast spells for X duration. This ability also interrupts spell casting. (I just love silences, taking away the ability to cast for a duration even if its short is a game changer.)

 

7.      Control Breath

You slow your target’s breathing and calm their mind, reducing the likelihood that they will assist their allies in battle. (Roamers are a real thing in Pantheon, this is a must prior to an engagement or post if you see a roamer coming close. Your job as a charmer is to control the battle field.)

 

8.     Shock and Awe

Confuse your target with bizarre imaginings, causing them to attack the nearest enemy for a short time.(AWESOME! So you have a Charmed pet, and now your using more enemies to gang up on the poor soul, love this build!)

 

9.     Mesmerize

 

You mesmerize your target, completely incapacitating them for X duration. The duration of this effect can be increased based on your Charisma and Constitution. Any damage will break the effect.(Since Dire Charm is an upgrade, I’m going to add this in. Mez should be used any time a roamer comes near, or you feel as if you might get over powered by adds. It’s the best way to take control of a situation.)         
 

Mana Battery – Most of us have heard of the enchanter being the “Mana Battery” in groups. This means the primary role of the build is to return as much MANA back to it’s group members as possible! Healers, Casters, even Melee, love having Mana Batteries in there group as the fights can go on longer, roamers become easier as group members are less likely to become Out Of Mana. DPS classes can go all out, as the tank can taunt more frequently without fear of going OOM. It has so many benefits it’s hard to fit them all in! This will be a short list, as the build is straight forward, no point in adding more spells for the sake of adding right?

 

Primary Stat – Dex (Every Crit landed with Rend the Mind is increased mana returned to the group)

 

Secondary Stat – Int/Char (Base damage is great also for Rend the Mind. Having a larger Mana Pool will allow you to cast your Mana Returning spells for a longer period of time.)

 

1.       Rend the Mind

You rend your target’s mind with a burst of mental energy, dealing Magic damage and restoring some Mana to you and your group members. (Obviously a staple to this build, returning Mana is the key and this is a great way to do it! The recommended stats will also give great opportunity for large spikes of mana to be returned per crit landed.)

 

2.     Enshire’s Faint Whisper

You enchant your ally’s mind with serenity, causing them to relax and allowing their Mana to regenerate more quickly. (I’m not sure if this can only be applied to one Ally or multiples, but this has to be up at all times on your healers! Your goal to to allow them to heal as long as possible, giving the tank a great leg to stand on.)

 

3.     Forceful Will

You dominate your target’s will, reducing their Magic Resistance by X and giving it to yourself for Y duration.(The mana returned is based on damage done, so set up the enemy prior to casting Rend The Mind, to get the maximum out-put from the target.)

 

4.     Mesmerize

You mesmerize your target, completely incapacitating them for X duration. The duration of this effect can be increased based on your Charisma and Constitution. Any damage will break the effect. (Still essential to have even though your primary role is returning mana.)

 

5.      Illusion Graft: Acuity

You graft an illusion into your ally’s mind, granting them an increased sense of mental acuity. While active, your ally’s Spell-Casting Speed will be increased by X%.(Casting this on yourself is perfect, turn you into a machine gun of mana returning.)

 

6.     Malison’s Crushing Grip

 

Applies intense pressure to your target’s brain, causing Magic damage over time. While active, your target’s Magic Resistance will decrease by X every Y seconds.(Apply this after Forceful Will to lower the magic resistance even further before you start spamming Rend The Mind. Make sure this is up during the entire length of an encounter.)
 

Debuff/Illusion Chanter – This build is build around the strong Debuffs the Enchanter can produce. Weaking an enemy can be just as strong as buffing your ally’s.

 

Primary Stat – Char (Increased mana pool will allow you to keep debuffs up throughout the long fights.)

 

Secondary Stat(s) – Int (This will help with any offensive abilities you use)

1.       Squee’s Mimicry

You cast an illusion, taking on the likeness of a random object in the environment within X meters of you. This illusion is quite effective and will fool most NPCs who see you, causing them to ignore you. (If there is a large patrol in the area you need to avoid, this will be key! It upgrades to Squee’s Grand Foolery for a full group effect.)

 

1.       Malison’s Crushing Grip

Applies intense pressure to your target’s brain, causing Magic damage over time. While active, your target’s Magic Resistance will decrease by X every Y seconds. (Lower the Magic resist giving those casters in the group a chance to lay waste to the enemy as you apply a DoT.)

 

2.     Illusion Graft: Exhaustion

You graft an illusion into your enemy’s mind, overwhelming them with the sense of exhaustion. While active, your enemy’s Strength and Agility will be reduced by X and their Attack Speed will be reduced by Y%. (An awesome Debuff lowing the mobs base damage, base AC, and attack speed. A great triple debuffs that effects essential stats for the enemy to damage your tank.)

 

3.     Eyumai’s Dulling

You weaken the materials in your enemy’s weapons, lowering the damage they are capable of dealing. (Another great debuff that lowers the damage your tank will receive!)

 

4.     Hush

Silences your enemy, making them unable to cast spells for X duration. This ability also interrupts spell casting. (Taking away the capability to cast a spell is incredibly strong and needs to be taken advantage of at all opportunities.)

 

5.      Forceful Will

You dominate your target’s will, reducing their Magic Resistance by X and giving it to yourself for Y duration. (Another reduction to Magic resist, Wizards are going to LOVE you!)

 

6.     Control Breath

You slow your target’s breathing and calm their mind, reducing the likelihood that they will assist their allies in battle. (This is a debuff even though it’s not stat oriented, in Pantheon you wlll come across mobs that are linked, so if one is pulled the other will follow, and it will eat up less mana than a Mez.)

 

7.      Thought Thief

You infiltrate the short-term memory of your target and completely erase their Hate list.(This is a nice hate debuff, that can be used if you have 2 tanks that need to switch, or if a rouge/wizzy is getting to much aggro and you need to restart the taunt process for your tank.)

 

8.     Rend the Mind

 

You rend your target’s mind with a burst of mental energy, dealing Magic damage and restoring some Mana to you and your group members. (If your able to throw an offensive spell in, might as well return mana to your group right?!?!)
 

OUTRO
